image.altText: An Italian women's footballer extends her right leg after taking a shot as the ball flies past an Argentina defender.

items.synopsis: End-to-end action, two goals ruled out for offside - and nothing official on the scoresheet yet in an exciting encounter between Italy and Argentina. Follow along in our live blog.

title.children: Plenty of action but no goals at the break between Italy, Argentina at Women's World Cup

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: You don't get a much more entertaining 0-0 than that. Italy have tried to dominate the ball but Argentina never let them get particularly comfortable. We've seen both sides intent on attacking, with Giacinti looking in the mood up front for Italy and Tefi Banini popping up everywhere for Argentina. There has been a fair bit of niggle too. What more could you want? Goals, I suppose.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: Italy 0 - 0  Argentina

children.content: You don't get a much more entertaining 0-0 than that. Italy have tried to dominate the ball but Argentina never let them get particularly comfortable. We've seen both sides intent on attacking, with Giacinti looking in the mood up front for Italy and Tefi Banini popping up everywhere for Argentina.
There has been a fair bit of niggle too.
What more could you want? Goals, I suppose.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: We are GO at Eden Park.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Italy vs Argentina is underway!

children.content: We are GO at Eden Park.
